 (x) = u\u03b4(x). The eigenstates n of the unperturbed Hamiltonian\n\nH(x, p; \u221e) are those of the left box together with those of the right box. We want to have an explicit expression\n\nfor the perturbation Wnm due to the coupling at x = 0.", "embedding": [-0.01899325, 0.028027168, 0.04124839, -0.010559979, -0.017102938, -0.027204527, -0.0047578686, 0.012059317, -0.05724089, 0.109416574, 0.047648765, 0.01610028, 0.004405632, -0.024420025, -0.03507864, 0.028465996, -0.015718061, 0.006083379, -0.07943568, 0.03813527, 0.01394489, 0.0071184277, -0.051418096, 0.0016228404, -0.03636201, 0.04574551, 0.013964436, 0.008748581, 0.041145973, 0.018951284, 0.011711086, -0.010354522, 0.010447923, -0.048202574, 0.0028375785, -0.009992487, -0.0062730424, -0.07729308, 0.01288695, -0.043718003, 0.04372121, 0.0014639755, -0.028176425, -0.034046408, -0.016481727, -0.011346569, -0.027659863, 0.0007024811, -0.07333413, -0.07983171, -0.017215477, -0.007065239, 0.03735935, -0.013617223, -0.014850275, 0.011687005, -0.014523172, 0.029380498, 0.0014276265, 0.02887319, 0.004339773, -0.023505313, 0.018736249, -0.01177008, 0.0035074519, 0.024744093, -0.0031975363, 0.05294682, 0.014731292, -0.017950589, -0.022698138, -0.011804171, -0.011640475, -0.028990613, -0.027621947, 0.050945573, 0.038329683, -0.02847848, -0.02606782, 0.0007943144, 0.026021501, 0.0027651468, -0.015482961, 0.010734825, -0.021093922, 0.022586726, -0.021455586, 0.0151112825, 0.012693564, -0.011445306, 0.033375483, 0.057142347, 0.04156534, 0.013903612, 0.026390752, 0.010020788, -0.017594311, 0.038642727, 0.03201804, 0.013778489, -0.01570211, 0.058896504, -0.008167599, 0.026431056, -0.022369996, 0.055029813, 0.0020561425, 0.0389527, 0.014809805, -0.052367892, 0.027199086, -0.029690845, -8.6801556e-05, 0.019311137, -0.020691408, 0.035982795, -0.014009637, 0.002050636, -0.021292537, -0.040179852, 0.019316306, 0.028488195, 0.040844988, 0.025330573, 0.00057668774, -0.0031551856, 0.013174406, -0.006907432, -0.052109174, -0.0024